column3: A data property that assigns a default integer value for a measurement datum to take on in case that the measurement cannot be carried out due to the fact that the material to be measured is not present or incomplete.
column5: This data property was introduced because the more generic superproperty http://w3id.org/rdfbones/core#hasMissingMaterialValue inherits the range rdfs:Literal from its superproperty http://w3id.org/rdfbones/core#hasDefaultValue while for implementation in AnthroGraph specification of an xsd datatype is required.
